title: Independent candidate Sultan-e-Rum wins PK-09 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Sultan-e-Rum has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-09 Swat-VII by securing 28,525 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was PTIP candidate Mohib Ullah Khan who bagged 6,913 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 31.67 per cent.
